main event: A civilian observed a round white object, presumed to be a satellite, moving across the sky over Plainview, New York.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size of a star., The observation lasted for about 5 to 10 minutes., The object was moving faster than normal for a star., The course of the object was to the northeast., The sighting occurred at a 25-degree elevation angle.
location: Plainview, L. I., New York, USA
witness description: 24-year-old male, electronics technician, occupation in avionics.
